          <Comment>This sequence change creates a premature translational stop signal (p.Arg38Glufs*7) in the SMAD4 gene. It is expected to result in an absent or disrupted protein product. Loss-of-function variants in SMAD4 are known to be pathogenic (PMID: 16152648, 16436638, 22810475). This variant is not present in population databases (gnomAD no frequency). This variant has not been reported in the literature in individuals affected with SMAD4-related conditions. For these reasons, this variant has been classified as Pathogenic.</Comment>
